  "A financial penalty or tax levied against companies that exceed permitted pollution emission thresholds": "",
  "A field measurement technique used exclusively for quantifying biodiversity within a given ecosystem": "",
  "A specialized engineering method used for cleaning up and remediating contaminated industrial waste sites": "",
  "An EIA is a systematic process required by law (under NEPA in the US) that evaluates the likely environmental consequences of a proposed project and explores alternatives and mitigation measures.": "",
